# PART 1: Create Maven Project

## Step 1: Create folder

```bash
mkdir Lab10
cd Lab10
```

---

## Step 2: Create Maven project

```bash
mvn archetype:generate \
-DgroupId=com.devops.lab \
-DartifactId=AzurePipeline \
-DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart \
-DinteractiveMode=false
```

Wait for:

```
BUILD SUCCESS
```

---

## Step 3: Go to project

```bash
cd AzurePipeline
ls
```

You should see:

```
pom.xml  src
```

---

## Step 4: Edit pom.xml

```bash
nano pom.xml
```

Add inside `<properties>`:

```xml
<properties>
    <maven.compiler.source>18</maven.compiler.source>
    <maven.compiler.target>18</maven.compiler.target>
    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>
</properties>
```

Save:

```
CTRL + X → Y → ENTER
```

(as shown in page 1) 

---

# PART 2: Push Code to Azure Repos

---

## Step 5: Open Azure DevOps

Go to your Azure DevOps:

* Open your organization
* Open your project

Then go:

```
Repos → Files → Initialize
```

(as shown in page 1–2 screenshots) 

---

## Step 6: Get repository URL

Click:

```
Clone → Copy HTTPS URL
```

---

## Step 7: Create Personal Access Token

Go to:

```
User Settings → Personal Access Token → New Token
```

Fill:

* Name: anything
* Scope:

  * Code → Read & Write
  * Agent Pools → Read & Manage

Copy token (IMPORTANT)

(as shown in page 3) 

---

## Step 8: Push code from terminal

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin <your-repo-url>
git branch -M master
git push -u origin master
```

When asked:

* Username → your Azure username
* Password → paste PAT token

---

# PART 3: Create Azure Pipeline

---

## Step 9: Create pipeline

Go to:

```
Pipelines → Create Pipeline
```

---

## Step 10: Select repository

Choose:

```
Azure Repos Git
```

Select your repository

(as shown in page 4) 

---

## Step 11: Configure pipeline

Choose:

```
Starter Pipeline
```

---

## Step 12: Replace YAML

Delete everything and paste:

```yaml
trigger:
- master

pool:
  name: Default

steps:
- task: Maven@3
  inputs:
    mavenPomFile: 'AzurePipeline/pom.xml'
    goals: 'clean install'
    publishJUnitResults: true
    testResultsFiles: '**/surefire-reports/TEST-*.xml'
```

(as shown in page 5) 

---

## Step 13: Save and Run

Click:

```
Save and Run
```

It may fail because agent is not configured.

---

# PART 4: Create Agent Pool

---

## Step 14: Go to Agent Pools

```
Organization Settings → Agent Pools → Default
```

(as shown page 5–6) 

---

## Step 15: Create Agent (Linux)

In terminal:

```bash
mkdir myagent && cd myagent
```

Download agent (from Azure UI instructions)

```bash
tar zxvf vsts-agent-linux-x64-*.tar.gz
```

---

## Step 16: Configure agent

```bash
./config.sh
```

Enter:

```
URL: https://dev.azure.com/your-org
Authentication: PAT
Token: (paste PAT)
Agent pool: Default
Agent name: anything
Work folder: ENTER
```

(as shown in page 7) 

---

## Step 17: Run agent

```bash
./run.sh
```

DO NOT close terminal

(as shown in page 8) 

---

## Step 18: Verify agent

Go to:

```
Organization Settings → Agent Pools → Default
```

You should see agent **online**

---

# PART 5: Run Pipeline

---

## Step 19: Run pipeline

Go to:

```
Pipelines → Run → Save and Run
```

If permission required:

```
Click View → Permit
```

(as shown in page 9) 

---

